with natalie cole sung here with one of his three backup singers 
the evening began with 20 minutes by comic michael winslow whose 
forte is making noises into a microphone of door locks a dog a 
car an airplane hes clever with an engaging manner and one 
would enjoy him more if not worried that one of his shrieks would 
pierce an eardrum 
regina belle a singer in the general style of anita baker had 
the middle slot between the two intermissions she has the voice 
the range the vocal stamina and the stage presence to hold and 
excite the audience with each song 
she doesnt yet have what jackson does the thread that ties 
different songs together and makes each one belong to the singer 
whos singing them 
