<TEXT>
while insisting that its problem with 
murderous drug traffickers is due to americans craving for cocaine 
colombia is finding it has a drug abuse problem of its own 
more than one in 10 colombians use drugs regularly and almost 5 
percent of children age 12 and younger have tried them according to 
an as yet unreleased government study obtained by the associated 
press 
when the drug use study conducted by the ministry of education is 
made public it is bound to shock this proud latin american country 
many colombians are fond of saying that drug abuse violence and 
lust for pornography are problems characterizing americans 
colombian society prides itself on its traditional values such as 
family unity and respect for elders 
president virgilio barco in speeches in washington and on 
nationwide television has repeated his message tirelessly united 
states drug users are ultimately to blame for drug trafficking in 
colombia 
the colombian government does not have a national program to 
prevent or treat drug addiction but it is spending money on 
advertising pointing to american addicts 
an ad being run in current government magazines and picked up by 
newspapers shows what is supposed to be a frecklefaced american 
woman snorting cocaine through a straw 
because of her cocaine habit she is directly supporting the 
drug terrorists who are tearing apart our country the ad says 
shes like thousands of young americans rich and poor alike 
addicted to cocaine 
the statistics of the colombian study are based upon lengthy 
questionnaires given to 7513 colombians from a wide social and 
geographic spectrum 
the study said 45 percent of colombians age 12 and under have 
tried drugs and gave these figures for young people of other age 
groups 
1315 years old 208 percent 
1618 years old 471 percent 
1921 years old 595 percent 
the most frequently used drugs in order of use are marijuana 
basuco cocaine heroin hashish lsd and even hallucinogenic 
mushrooms the study says 
basuco is the brown residue scraped from the inside of a 
container after preparing cocaine base it is smoked like crack 
cocaine base has not yet been treated with hydrochloric acid for 
making pure cocaine and is therefore said to be weaker than crack 
the results of the colombian study were so shocking that a 
followup study was done of 30000 colombians age 15 and older to 
see how many use drugs on a steady basis the head of the education 
ministry study gabriel gutierrez garcia told the ap 
twelve percent of those questioned use illegal drugs on a regular 
basis the study showed according to gutierrez 
there is no visible federal campaign against drug use in 
colombia whatever minor programs there are scattered throughout the 
country are supposed to directed and coordinated by colombias 
national drug council 
however one of the councils administrators maria mercedes 
sanchez said she did not know how much the government spends on 
drug prevention 
there is nothing identifiable in the colombian governments 
budget for prevention and treatment of drug addiction 
ap inquiries about government drug programs that might exist did 
not turn up a single program 
the health ministry contributes 2500 a year to operation of the 
countrys largest drug rehabilitation clinic the director of the 
clinic in bogota maria isabel salagar de lince told the ap 
it isnt much but every little bit helps she said in an 
interview about the clinic that treats 1000 people a year she said 
the bogota clinic is privately run and nonprofit 
mrs lince said she believes there are 10 other clinics in the 
country but knows nothing about them she said the national drug 
council emphasizes drug enforcment rather than prevention and cure 
the government has no drug rehabiliation centers 
bogota mayor andres pastrana elected last year for a twoyear 
term has created a corps of 75 psychologists and 25 other workers 
to inform teachers and pupils about the dangers of drug addiction 
gloria inez garcia an administrator with the program told the ap 
there are no federal programs against drug addicition or for 
helping cure people of addiction miss garcia said in an interview 
as for the bogota mayors program it is unlikely it will survive 
when pastrana is replaced next august 
colombian mayors elected every two years cannot run for 
reelection and new mayors almost always wipe out the social 
programs of predecessors 
the most visible nationwide campaign against drug addiction was 
by colombias privately owned banco cafetero coffee growers bank 
three years ago posters billboards and radio and television spots 
warned people of the dangers of drug addiction 
on television an actor portraying a drug addict changed on the 
screen from normallooking to beastly 
the colombian government often relies on the private sector to 
assume responsibility for such campaigns even signs announcing to 
drivers that a military base lies ahead often carries accompanying 
advertising by the company that paid for the sign 
access to drugs in colombia is literally as easy as buying a 
hotdog from a street vendor it is common knowledge the vendors sell 
drugs 
an ap reporter living here 10 years has seen farmers making 
cocaine base in small open laboratories in the jungle and the high 
andes mountains 
the operations are widespread with farmers often testing their 
product before sending it by a motorcycle messenger to the nearest 
city 
drugs are cheap here a kilo 22 pounds of cocaine costs just 
1100 in bogota compared to 11000 to 15000 in miami 
in discotheques in wealthy parts of the capital of bogota a city 
of 6 million people customers openly buy cocaine and other drugs 
from waiters or pay a waiter to have the doorman go out and buy them 
it is easy and simple to buy drugs on the street without even 
knowing anyone certain streets are wellknown for drug trafficking 
and a prospective buyer has only to touch his forehead with his 
right hand to signal a horde of drug vendors 
</TEXT>
