high winds and torrential rains 
tuesday killed seven people and left thousands homeless in southern 
brazil according to globo television 
all seven died in parana state where flooding mudslides and 
winds also swept away homes and knocked out power lines 
in the state capital of curitiba 520 miles southwest of rio 
three people drowned in the outlying provinces at least four 
people died in flooding said globo the nations largest private 
network 
in the remote town of aparecida do oeste 20 people were hurt 
when 65 mph winds toppled a brick and wood church during a morning 
service 
in the neighboring states of santa catarina and rio grande do 
sul which border uruguay and argentina high winds and mudslides 
leveled houses knocked out power and blocked roadways 
thousands of slum dwellers left homeless in the three states were 
sheltered in schools and churches the network said 
