for more than a decade edward i koch led new 
york with a brash often combative style when he faced his last 
hurrah on tuesday he accepted defeat graciously and called his 
years in office glorious 
with his loss to manhattan borough president david dinkins in the 
democratic primary the 64yearold mayor was denied his goal of 
becoming the first fourterm mayor in the citys history 
i have had 12 glorious years as mayor koch declared in his 
concession speech urging his supporters not to feel sorry for him 
he said believe me there is a life after the mayoralty 
traditionally new yorks mayor is a national political figure 
but koch with his smartaleck remarks his eye for the television 
cameras his zest for his office became a worldwide celebrity 
he wrote a bestseller mayor and two other books he 
appeared on saturday night live he was interviewed in playboy 
and he was quoted ad infinitum jimmy carters brother billy 
was a wacko developer donald trump was piggy piggy piggy 
jews would have to be crazy to vote for jesse jackson 
that nasal feisty voice was unknown to most new yorkers when 
koch ran for mayor in 1977 his name was recognized by only 6 
percent of new yorkers outside of his congressional district 
koch the bronxborn son of polish immigrants had been active in 
liberal democratic politics in 1963 he defeated party boss carmine 
desapio in a race for district leader he was elected to the city 
council in 1966 and to congress from manhattans silk stocking 
district in 1968 
a 1973 campaign for mayor foundered after 45 days for lack of 
money and 1977 did not look much more encouraging he faced seven 
