<TEXT>
the alexandrov red army song and dance ensemble 
put together a program clearly intended to win americans audiences 
it starts with the the star spangled banner and ends with god 
bless america and in between are not only russian folk songs but 
other internationalisms including a soloist who sounds like an irish 
tenor 
the company opened tuesday night for eight performances at the 
city center next it goes to 29 other american cities 
the troupe has swashbuckling dancers men and women in 
colorful folk costumes crowded behind the dancing space the 
orchestra has russian instruments including balalaika and dombra 
and western symphony instruments 
most impressive of all to this member of the audience was the 
male chorus of more than 80 voices members of the chorus stood on 
four rows of risers at the back of the stage their prominent sound 
was baritone when they hummed in harmony it was glorious 
soloists were tenors and baritones the russian deep bass voice 
