we have not been able to come up with a way that would not 
involve significant shortterm costs enoff told a subcommittee of 
the house select committee on aging 
under current law workers aged 65 trrough 69 lose 1 in social 
security benefits for every 2 they earn above 8880 the limit is 
6480 for workers under age 65 and there is no limit for those 70 
or older 
in 1990 benefits for those aged 6569 will be reduced 1 for 
every 3 earned above the limit 
