treatment plant that is part of the 61 billion boston harbor 
cleanup 
massachusetts water resources authority officials said it was the 
first time such bunkers have been demolished 
the fort dawes bunkers date back to 1942 during world war ii 
all the islands within broad sound the main shipping channel into 
boston harbor contained manned forts after the war ended in 1945 
the navy used the bunkers for storage 
the first of the bunkers was blown up with 9200 pounds of 
