east german refugees say they were tired of political repression 
and economic stagnation 
in a formal protest tuesday east germany accused hungary of 
violating bilateral agreements and interfering with east german 
sovereignty czechoslovakia and romania also were critical 
hungarys foreign ministry in a terse note carried by the 
official mti news agency said wednesday it would extensively 
contradict the east german accusations it did not say when 
as part of its reforms hungary became the first soviet bloc 
nation to join the un convention on refugees rights it came into 
force june 12 and officials have said they plan to change domestic 
laws and international agreements to dovetail with the accord 
with its release of the east german refugees hungary suspended a 
1969 agreement with east germany which in effect stipulated that no 
east german could leave for the west without east berlins 
permission 
somogyi said similar agreements with other warsaw pact countries 
are no longer in line with our newly assumed international 
responsibilities 
but officials have insisted for months that hungary does not 
intend to become a springboard to the west 
somogyi said anybody including citizens of soviet bloc nations 
could apply for refugee status and would be given a fair hearing 
he emphasized that the current situation was temporary and limited 
to east germans 
this decision to allow east german citizens to leave for the 
west was a unique step he said it pertains only to east german 
citizens and in no way can it be interpreted as applying to 
citizens of other warsaw pact nations 
he said hungary in the future will work under the criteria of the 
geneva convention forbidding signatories to return to their 
countries refugees whose life or freedom would be threatened on 
account of his race religion nationality or political 
opinion 
signatories also can only allow the exit of refugees welcomed by 
a third country west germany recognizes all east germans as 
citizens but few nations are willing to accept refugees from 
romania bulgaria and czechoslovakia which have also been slow to 
introduce reform 
officials have acknowledged that tensions with romania were 
partially responsible for hungarys decision to join the convention 
hungary began sheltering romanian refugees in january 1988 breaking 
an agreement with its southeastern neighbor to send back citizens 
seeking asylum 
about 17000 romanian nationals have fled most of them ethnic 
hungarians in the first instance of one warsaw pact country giving 
permanent sanctuary to citizens of another on grounds of alleged 
persecution 
