rupert murdoch entered the bidding 
for mgmua communication co on wednesday with an offer that values 
the company at 18 billion topping a rival 164 billion bid by an 
australian entertainment group 
the bid was made by the media magnates news corp ltd and its 
20th century fox film corp subsidiary 
analysts said murdoch apparently wants mgmuas huge film 
library which he could use for his fox tv network here and sky 
television satellite operation in europe 
mgmua had agreed to sell its united artists assets to an 
affiliate of qintex australia ltd by the end of this month in a 
deal that valued mgmuas stock at about 124 billion 160 million 
less than the new offer of 14 billion according to mgmua 
spokeswoman mary hardy 
she said the buyer would also assume about 400 million in debt 
mgmua said fox and news corp had offered 2316 for each of the 
approximately 53 million shares of mgmua common stock and 18 per 
share for the more than 10 million shares of preferred stock qintex 
had offered 20 for each common share and 18 per preferred share 
shares of mgmua common stock closed tuesday at 1975 on the new 
york stock exchange a high for the year then surged to 21125 per 
share by the close of trading wednesday qintex plunged 2 to close 
at 6 per share wednesday in overthecounter trading 
confirmation of a rumor earlier wednesday that murdoch was the 
bidder did not come until after the market closed 
news corps american depositary shares are traded on the nyse 
and slipped 12 cents to 25 a share wednesday each news corp ads 
is equivalent to two shares of the australian companys common 
shares 
fox spokesman dennis petroskey confirmed the offer but refused 
to discuss how it would be financed or other issues saying only 
we are in discussions with mgmua we will have no further comment 
