<TEXT>
the us dollar edged down against the japanese yen 
thursday morning while share prices on the tokyo stock exchange 
inched up 
the nikkei stock average of 225 selected issues regained 3059 
points or 009 percent ending morning trading at 3431753 the 
index had shed 4594 points the previous day 
the dollar ended morning trading at 14575 yen it started 
trading at 14605 yen down 065 yen from wednesdays 14670yen 
close and moved in a range of 14550 to 14643 yen 
currency dealers attributed the dollars lower opening to its 
overnight downswing mainly against major european currencies on 
overseas markets 
the dollar started falling against the yen as foreign investors 
sold it against the west german mark said a bank of tokyo trader 
speaking on condition of anonymity 
the currency fell further as the bank of japan conducted a 
dollarselling intervention to halt the dollars excessive rise when 
some investors attempted to buy it back he said 
the bank of japan reportedly sold some 300 million the central 
bank does not comment on its monetary actions 
other traders said many market players were sitting on the 
sidelines as the market awaited a spate of major us economic 
figures this week 
among major data to be released by the us government were the 
nations august retail sales due out later thursday in washington 
and the july merchandise trade figures due friday 
on the stock exchange the markets key index rose as market 
players were reassured by the yens recovery against the dollar 
said kazuyuki suzuki a daiwa securities dealer 
the yens rebound pushed down the shortterm interest rate 
here which also reassured participants and encouraged them to buy 
stocks he said 
but trading was light ahead of a threeday weekend starting 
friday respect for the aged day a national holiday suzuki said 
